1
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:08,292
Ploy Ying and I are truly dating.

2
00:00:08,292 --> 00:00:10,511
And from today on, I will stand by her

3
00:00:10,817 --> 00:00:12,333
the way a man should.

4
00:00:12,533 --> 00:00:14,133
I can entrust my daughter to you.

5
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:16,866
Auntie Headman… absolutely.

6
00:00:17,366 --> 00:00:19,928
We have to start from what is truly us,

7
00:00:20,336 --> 00:00:21,933
or from what we once lost.

8
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,470
Guy, when I looked at your face today,

9
00:00:23,470 --> 00:00:25,766
I’d never seen you
this happy before.

10
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:30,748
Did you hear that?

11
00:00:31,207 --> 00:00:33,133
The investors aren’t continuing their funding.

12
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,501
If my dream disappears again,

13
00:00:36,929 --> 00:00:38,468
what will you say?

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,291
Bazaar Bangkok
to restructure shareholders

15
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,292
Have investors really withdrawn funding?

16
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:49,933
Why doesn’t this news have a clear source?

17
00:00:50,244 --> 00:00:51,200
No information found.

18
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,300
But it was deleted unusually fast.

19
00:01:16,166 --> 00:01:17,766
It rained all night last night.

20
00:01:19,066 --> 00:01:20,133
You couldn’t sleep, could you?

21
00:01:20,766 --> 00:01:21,566
Yeah.

22
00:01:22,266 --> 00:01:24,500
I feel like something is definitely wrong.

23
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,666
So last night, I looked into the investors.

24
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,601
I saw that the investors

25
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,165
pulled their funding early last month.

26
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:35,000
But our company only went quiet two days ago.

27
00:01:41,866 --> 00:01:44,166
Do you think it’ll affect our series?

28
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:49,436
I don’t think anyone will say it directly.

29
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,415
But last night, I had a dream.

30
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:55,820
I dreamed it was raining,
and all the lights on set went out.

31
00:01:57,766 --> 00:01:58,666
Me too.

32
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,066
Just in a different place.

33
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:07,566
I think if it really happens,

34
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:10,133
we have to be ready for it.

35
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,366
Keep every document complete.

36
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,666
Contract copies, project files,
and promo posts.

37
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,333
We won’t let
our dream disappear.

38
00:02:25,966 --> 00:02:26,739
I agree.

39
00:02:27,402 --> 00:02:28,713
It won’t hurt to be prepared.

40
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:35,422
Urgent meeting at 14:00.

41
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:40,966
They’ve called us in for a meeting.

42
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:43,966
Then

43
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:48,666
let’s go together today.

44
00:02:52,243 --> 00:02:53,886
Yeah. Together.

45
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:56,166
Like always.

46
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,400
As for calling you here urgently today,

47
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:27,300
there’s nothing much.

48
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,368
Some things may be changing lately.

49
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:33,472
Don’t worry.

50
00:04:34,798 --> 00:04:36,423
Everything is still according to plan.

51
00:04:37,766 --> 00:04:38,786
I understand.

52
00:04:38,786 --> 00:04:40,877
But we can really feel

53
00:04:40,877 --> 00:04:43,104
that the atmosphere isn’t
the same anymore.

54
00:04:43,512 --> 00:04:46,317
And there are bad rumors
about the company too.

55
00:04:47,933 --> 00:04:50,733
We just want to know
what’s going on.

56
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,933
They’re just shifting positions a little.

57
00:04:55,766 --> 00:04:57,166
This industry moves fast.

58
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,333
Sometimes things have to change to survive.

59
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:01,133
And about the rumor

60
00:05:02,566 --> 00:05:04,766
that our company is changing its main investor,

61
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:06,666
is that true?

62
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,400
Rumors are rumors.

63
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:18,266
Don’t overthink it, Guy.

64
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,266
Our company is still the same.

65
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:21,966
The two of you

66
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,400
just focus on acting.

67
00:05:25,566 --> 00:05:27,333
But if things really aren’t the same anymore,

68
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,466
we just want to know.

69
00:05:29,733 --> 00:05:31,500
At least we can prepare properly.

70
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,733
You’re overthinking it.

71
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:45,000
These matters are handled by the higher-ups.

72
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:46,966
Don’t worry just yet.

73
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:49,766
Soon, there’ll be good news.

74
00:05:51,266 --> 00:05:52,066
Just wait a little.

75
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:04,233
Hey.

76
00:06:04,845 --> 00:06:08,060
Do you believe what they said?

77
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:11,997
Not completely.

78
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:13,774
One thing is certain.

79
00:06:13,978 --> 00:06:16,217
They’re hiding something from us.

80
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:25,800
Then what should we do?

81
00:06:28,866 --> 00:06:30,700
For now, we’ll have to wait and see

82
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:35,466
which light goes out first.

83
00:06:51,634 --> 00:06:54,042
One week later

84
00:06:54,042 --> 00:06:57,266
After the agency expanded too fast

85
00:06:57,766 --> 00:06:58,545
Shit.

86
00:06:59,565 --> 00:07:01,282
Is the news real?

87
00:07:02,812 --> 00:07:03,498
It’s real.

88
00:07:04,359 --> 00:07:05,760
They officially announced it.

89
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:08,555
That means

90
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,200
our company is closing.

91
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:12,166
What should we do?

92
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:16,880
Hey.

93
00:07:17,696 --> 00:07:18,472
I think first of all,

94
00:07:18,931 --> 00:07:20,330
we shouldn’t panic yet.

95
00:07:20,942 --> 00:07:22,090
The first thing we need to do

96
00:07:22,753 --> 00:07:25,713
is gather every work-related document.

97
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:29,873
Employment contract copies
and promo posts.

98
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,651
You already thought of all this?

99
00:07:34,966 --> 00:07:35,766
Yeah.

100
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:38,400
When I saw the company becoming unstable,

101
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:40,333
I had already prepared myself a little.

102
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,384
This industry survives because of people,

103
00:07:44,302 --> 00:07:45,482
not because of agencies.

104
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,933
Then what do we do?

105
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:56,200
The series just finished filming.

106
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,200
It hasn’t even released all its episodes yet.

107
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,118
Hey.

108
00:08:01,781 --> 00:08:04,343
Our series will probably air every episode.

109
00:08:05,057 --> 00:08:06,001
It’s just…

110
00:08:06,817 --> 00:08:10,183
after this, PR and promotion

111
00:08:11,152 --> 00:08:14,070
and the social media team
won’t be like before.

112
00:08:16,671 --> 00:08:18,100
We have to help ourselves now.

113
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,966
You mean we have to do our own PR?

114
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:30,720
Don’t forget, we already have a
fanbase and viewers.

115
00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:33,269
We just need to communicate clearly

116
00:08:33,575 --> 00:08:34,728
that we’re still here.

117
00:08:35,136 --> 00:08:38,221
Then they’ll help push us forward
so we can survive.

118
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:41,059
Then

119
00:08:42,181 --> 00:08:43,304
let’s make our series

120
00:08:44,069 --> 00:08:45,303
survive with our own hands.

121
00:08:46,731 --> 00:08:47,735
As for the agency,

122
00:08:48,245 --> 00:08:50,361
let’s set that aside for now, Guy.

123
00:08:51,483 --> 00:08:52,548
We haven’t stopped.

124
00:08:54,384 --> 00:08:56,538
We’re just starting again in our own way.

125
00:09:02,512 --> 00:09:03,288
Paused,

126
00:09:07,866 --> 00:09:08,966
but not stopped, right?

127
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:12,531
Definitely not stopped.

128
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,400
Hey.

129
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:35,920
Look at this.

130
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:36,420
What?

131
00:09:36,566 --> 00:09:37,366
Hey, what?

132
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:39,133
It’s news about Guy and Nine’s agency.

133
00:09:39,366 --> 00:09:40,200
Is it really closing?

134
00:09:40,866 --> 00:09:41,766
Let me see.

135
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,466
Pleng, call Guy right now.

136
00:09:47,766 --> 00:09:48,566
Okay. Okay.

137
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:06,133
Yes.

138
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:09,666
Please give us some time
to get ourselves together.

139
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:12,166
We’ll contact you back later.

140
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:14,100
Thank you.

141
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:15,733
Thank you.

142
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:19,266
But right now, we haven’t decided
on moving agencies yet.

143
00:10:20,133 --> 00:10:22,966
Once there’s clear news,
we’ll let you know.

144
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:25,100
Thank you.

145
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,466
I never thought so many people would call.

146
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,300
Pleng is calling.

147
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:48,100
Answer it.

148
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:50,100
I think he’s probably worried.

149
00:10:51,066 --> 00:10:51,866
Go ahead.

150
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:58,600
Guy, is it true?
The news that your agency went bankrupt.

151
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:00,800
It’s true.

152
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:04,116
But don’t worry.

153
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:06,941
We’re okay.

154
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:11,666
Everyone at home heard the news and got worried. Are you okay?

155
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,894
Right now, I’m with Nine.

156
00:11:15,557 --> 00:11:18,758
We’ve talked, and we’ll find a way through this.

157
00:11:19,574 --> 00:11:21,513
We won’t let our work disappear.

158
00:11:22,278 --> 00:11:25,172
Our work won’t disappear.

159
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,313
I’m

160
00:11:32,537 --> 00:11:33,777
about to invite the two of you

161
00:11:34,848 --> 00:11:37,031
to perform in Shining Love (Prakai Rak Song Jai) with us.

162
00:11:42,066 --> 00:11:43,043
Because

163
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:46,858
this story was written from our real lives.

164
00:11:47,434 --> 00:11:50,497
And if someone has to play Tor Prakai,

165
00:11:51,262 --> 00:11:54,003
it has to be the real Tor Prakai, right?

166
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,574
(Pleng Chai) That’s right.
(Lynchee) That’s right.

167
00:12:05,966 --> 00:12:06,766
P’Phet.

168
00:12:09,066 --> 00:12:11,133
Are you really asking me
to go back and perform Likay?

169
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:13,524
Yes.

170
00:12:14,493 --> 00:12:16,182
I want Guy to come back and perform with me.

171
00:12:17,355 --> 00:12:18,178
Because

172
00:12:19,504 --> 00:12:20,169
we

173
00:12:21,036 --> 00:12:29,268
are bringing our lives back to a real stage.

174
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:31,204
This will be huge news in the Likay industry.

175
00:12:31,816 --> 00:12:36,212
The return of a BL series leading man to a real
Likay stage.

176
00:12:36,866 --> 00:12:37,666
That sounds so worth watching.

177
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:38,566
Absolutely.

178
00:12:38,566 --> 00:12:39,943
Okay, then we

179
00:12:39,943 --> 00:12:42,966
will make fabulous, stunning comeback content.

180
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:43,566
Yeah.

181
00:12:43,566 --> 00:12:46,714
Then Lynchee and I will post the news
on our page.

182
00:12:46,714 --> 00:12:48,766
Faster than those gossip pages.

183
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:51,457
How about this? Let’s start with

184
00:12:51,457 --> 00:12:53,600
(Lynchee) posting handsome, stunning photos.
(Nine) See?

185
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:54,900
The fans are working harder than us.

186
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:56,300
The likes will shoot up.

187
00:12:56,966 --> 00:13:00,666
And I also want Nine to perform with our troupe too.

188
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:09,166
Because no one understands this story
better than we do.

189
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:17,666
This is a great opportunity.
Let’s try it.

190
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,333
Then announce it.

191
00:13:23,966 --> 00:13:25,533
We definitely won’t disappear.

192
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:53,088
Yeah, Pleng.

193
00:13:53,802 --> 00:13:54,633
I think

194
00:13:55,245 --> 00:13:57,449
I’ll have you try a new role.

195
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,644
You don’t have to be funny like before.

196
00:14:01,409 --> 00:14:03,896
A second lead who once made mistakes,

197
00:14:04,559 --> 00:14:06,398
but comes back to fight for his life,

198
00:14:06,959 --> 00:14:11,033
with true love kept deep in his heart.

199
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,666
The second lead?

200
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:16,700
Oh.

201
00:14:17,366 --> 00:14:18,533
So I’ll have to, like,

202
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:21,333
practice my serious look, right?

203
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:24,398
Yes, Pleng.

204
00:14:24,959 --> 00:14:28,202
It’s time for you to sing and dance about love

205
00:14:28,661 --> 00:14:30,527
and make the audience truly feel it.

206
00:14:30,527 --> 00:14:31,153
Mm.

207
00:14:31,153 --> 00:14:32,161
I can do it.

208
00:14:32,365 --> 00:14:33,678
Will this really work?

209
00:14:34,443 --> 00:14:37,455
It’s easier for me to make people laugh
than make them cry.

210
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:42,466
It shows another side of you.

211
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,700
So people can see

212
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,100
that funny people have hearts too.

213
00:14:46,866 --> 00:14:48,686
Oh.

214
00:14:48,966 --> 00:14:51,000
Then can I act too?

215
00:14:51,366 --> 00:14:52,766
I’ve wanted to for so long.

216
00:14:53,566 --> 00:14:54,666
What role should it be?

217
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:57,366
A city girl,

218
00:14:58,866 --> 00:15:01,312
so beautiful she steals a young man’s heart,

219
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:02,984
or maybe

220
00:15:03,239 --> 00:15:05,693
maybe a new heroine.

221
00:15:05,999 --> 00:15:07,331
I can do that too.

222
00:15:07,586 --> 00:15:09,001
Lynchee, you want to try acting, right?

223
00:15:09,307 --> 00:15:10,480
I think someone like you

224
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,542
suits the role of a city girl.

225
00:15:12,542 --> 00:15:14,851
Charming and talkative.

226
00:15:15,310 --> 00:15:16,936
Talks a lot and never stops.

227
00:15:17,191 --> 00:15:19,663
Dresses up in all kinds of styles,
and most importantly,

228
00:15:20,479 --> 00:15:21,322
not much dancing either.

229
00:15:21,832 --> 00:15:23,644
Interested? Want to try?

230
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:25,408
Then I’ll write the role for you.

231
00:15:25,612 --> 00:15:27,174
Really, P’Phet?

232
00:15:27,175 --> 00:15:28,410
Oh my God.

233
00:15:29,079 --> 00:15:30,387
I’m so happy.

234
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:32,166
I need to write this down first or I’ll forget.

235
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,533
Am I going to be famous?

236
00:15:35,566 --> 00:15:38,503
If Daddy finds out,
he’ll scream the house down for sure.

237
00:15:38,504 --> 00:15:39,523
Then,

238
00:15:39,523 --> 00:15:42,876
will my heroine position
be stolen?

239
00:15:42,876 --> 00:15:44,541
I won’t steal it, P’Ploy.

240
00:15:44,541 --> 00:15:45,133
You’re possessive.

241
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:50,066
We’ll make Shining Love (Prakai Rak Song Jai)
shine brighter than ever.

242
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:55,984
Why is my little sister

243
00:15:55,984 --> 00:15:57,866
not around Siam
on weekends anymore?

244
00:15:58,133 --> 00:15:59,638
Hey, P’Plub.

245
00:16:00,403 --> 00:16:01,953
I thought you were in Luang Prabang.

246
00:16:02,966 --> 00:16:03,766
How did you get here?

247
00:16:06,733 --> 00:16:09,311
Actually, I once told P’Plub

248
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,221
about this too.

249
00:16:11,425 --> 00:16:11,925
I said

250
00:16:12,231 --> 00:16:16,318
someone named Pleng Chai
would come see my father.

251
00:16:18,008 --> 00:16:19,085
Right?

252
00:16:19,647 --> 00:16:20,248
Hey.

253
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:22,723
P’Plub is calling.

254
00:16:23,366 --> 00:16:24,166
Perfect timing.

255
00:16:24,266 --> 00:16:25,066
Answer it first.

256
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:27,910
P’Plub.

257
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:29,359
Lynchee.

258
00:16:29,643 --> 00:16:31,213
I’ve arrived in Luang Prabang.

259
00:16:31,213 --> 00:16:32,949
I’ll be back in Thailand in a few days.

260
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,590
Oh, P’Plub.

261
00:16:34,896 --> 00:16:36,230
Do you remember I told you

262
00:16:36,230 --> 00:16:39,572
there would be a guest named
Pleng Chai coming to see Father?

263
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:40,500
Here.

264
00:16:42,445 --> 00:16:43,908
(Pleng Chai) Hello.
(Lynchee) Sorry, that was sudden.

265
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:45,489
Oh.

266
00:16:45,795 --> 00:16:47,389
The funny guy who’s a streamer

267
00:16:47,389 --> 00:16:49,051
and said he was going to court you?

268
00:16:49,051 --> 00:16:49,757
Yes.

269
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,660
That’s me.

270
00:16:51,966 --> 00:16:53,300
You’re Khun Ploy Ying, right?

271
00:16:54,300 --> 00:16:55,388
You’re graceful like

272
00:16:55,388 --> 00:16:56,853
the Likay heroine

273
00:16:56,853 --> 00:16:58,800
my father took me to watch when I was a child.

274
00:16:59,108 --> 00:17:00,000
Thank you.

275
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,613
Sharp eyes.

276
00:17:02,614 --> 00:17:04,002
I’m Phet Thae.

277
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:07,466
You could say
I’m Pleng Chai’s older brother.

278
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:09,147
Hello.

279
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,933
Then Thai and I would love
to visit the troupe sometime.

280
00:17:14,566 --> 00:17:15,533
I want to see the real thing.

281
00:17:17,266 --> 00:17:18,007
Hey.

282
00:17:18,415 --> 00:17:21,151
Come on over, and I’ll prepare
the full troupe for you.

283
00:17:21,152 --> 00:17:22,966
Wow.

284
00:17:22,966 --> 00:17:24,415
See you all soon.

285
00:17:24,415 --> 00:17:26,133
See you in Thailand.

286
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:28,000
Bye-bye, P’Plub.

287
00:17:28,166 --> 00:17:28,966
Goodbye.

288
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:31,900
Bye-bye.

289
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,100
I miss P’Plub.

290
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,133
He’s been gone so long.

291
00:17:35,166 --> 00:17:37,712
P’Plub is really smooth with words.

292
00:17:37,712 --> 00:17:41,166
If he opened a new channel,
he’d hit a million subs in no time.

293
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:46,466
Why are you hanging around
in front of the Likay troupe?

294
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:47,533
Very suspicious.

295
00:17:48,366 --> 00:17:50,166
You tease me as soon as you get back.

296
00:17:50,533 --> 00:17:51,333
Of course.

297
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,666
Just look, P’Plub.

298
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,166
The vibe is good.

299
00:17:54,966 --> 00:17:56,066
Everyone is kind.

300
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,166
And on top of that,

301
00:17:59,466 --> 00:18:02,400
P’Plub’s little sister
is about to become a new heroine.

302
00:18:03,066 --> 00:18:03,745
Really?

303
00:18:03,745 --> 00:18:04,300
Really.

304
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,266
I’m excited.

305
00:18:05,266 --> 00:18:07,466
P’Plub, you came at the perfect time.

306
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:10,533
Our troupe wants
fresh content for the page.

307
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:11,700
Hm?

308
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,533
P’Plub is expensive, you know.

309
00:18:15,906 --> 00:18:17,039
Thank you.

310
00:18:17,766 --> 00:18:19,100
Welcome home.

311
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:20,466
Yes.

312
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:24,266
Since I’m back,
I want to start from here.

313
00:18:24,878 --> 00:18:26,645
May I collect
information here?

314
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,186
And may I exchange payment by

315
00:18:29,696 --> 00:18:31,110
making vlogs for the troupe?

316
00:18:34,616 --> 00:18:37,608
That’s exactly what we need.
What do you think?

317
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:50,474
I’m about to invite the two of you

318
00:18:51,341 --> 00:18:53,988
to perform in Shining Love (Prakai Rak Song Jai)
with us.

319
00:18:58,266 --> 00:18:59,394
Congratulations

320
00:18:59,394 --> 00:19:01,422
on getting to stand with the Likay troupe again.

321
00:19:02,085 --> 00:19:05,708
And I get to try
something new too.

322
00:19:10,766 --> 00:19:12,600
Today, I have something to tell you.

323
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,200
That tone.

324
00:19:17,066 --> 00:19:18,133
Definitely not good news.

325
00:19:19,566 --> 00:19:20,120
Well…

326
00:19:20,936 --> 00:19:23,900
I’ve been suspicious
since the last workshop.

327
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,466
The atmosphere was strange.

328
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,833
After I came back,

329
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:30,666
I tried asking people at the channel.

330
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:32,900
And I got an answer.

331
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,466
An answer?

332
00:19:38,266 --> 00:19:38,766
The answer is

333
00:19:39,429 --> 00:19:41,621
our agency has been losing money
for three straight months.

334
00:19:42,029 --> 00:19:44,900
Accounting was ordered to delay payments
since the start of the month.

335
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:47,500
I just received the confirmation documents.

336
00:19:48,766 --> 00:19:50,766
All the investors have pulled out.

337
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:55,100
Hey.

338
00:19:56,766 --> 00:19:58,700
You knew everything before it became news?

339
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,533
I could roughly guess.

340
00:20:02,366 --> 00:20:04,066
So I found a backup plan first.

341
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,266
I contacted the channel

342
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,766
to ask them to release
every episode of our series.

343
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:12,400
If there are any cost issues,

344
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:14,100
they can deduct it from my pay.

345
00:20:18,266 --> 00:20:22,333
You went that far?

346
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:24,640
Hey.

347
00:20:25,507 --> 00:20:26,794
Even if I had to do more than this,

348
00:20:27,712 --> 00:20:28,981
I’d gladly do it.

349
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,515
This isn’t just about me alone.

350
00:20:33,096 --> 00:20:34,744
It’s our dream.

351
00:20:35,917 --> 00:20:38,227
I won’t let it end meaninglessly.

352
00:20:42,255 --> 00:20:43,712
Then I’ll help you too.

353
00:20:45,752 --> 00:20:48,237
Whether it’s PR,

354
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:51,275
posting, or talking to fans,

355
00:20:52,917 --> 00:20:54,151
I promise

356
00:20:56,133 --> 00:20:57,766
I’ll make sure people don’t forget us.

357
00:20:58,300 --> 00:20:59,733
That we made this work with our hearts.

358
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,000
Our dream must not go to waste.

359
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,566
I already believe in you.

360
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:08,898
As long as

361
00:21:09,357 --> 00:21:11,566
we don’t forget what we started with,

362
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,066
our dream is still alive.

363
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:35,566
Should we go live and talk to the fans?

364
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:40,100
Okay.

365
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:45,366
Then I’ll use my phone.

366
00:21:47,628 --> 00:21:48,200
Screaming! A couple live!

367
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,492
Hello, everyone.

368
00:21:49,493 --> 00:21:50,359
Hello.

369
00:21:50,359 --> 00:21:52,997
Thank you, everyone, for still staying
with the two of us.

370
00:21:52,997 --> 00:21:57,302
We’ve learned that
our agency has closed down.

371
00:21:57,302 --> 00:21:59,657
But I want everyone to rest assured.

372
00:22:00,266 --> 00:22:01,533
We’ll stay right here and go nowhere.

373
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:04,323
And please don’t worry.

374
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:06,533
Our series will definitely air every episode.

375
00:22:06,533 --> 00:22:09,564
Yes, and after our series ends,

376
00:22:10,338 --> 00:22:14,007
the two of us are working
on a project together.

377
00:22:14,386 --> 00:22:14,886
Keep fighting!

378
00:22:14,886 --> 00:22:15,386
Sending you support.

379
00:22:15,387 --> 00:22:15,887
I’ll follow you forever.

380
00:22:15,888 --> 00:22:16,388
Love you both.

381
00:22:16,388 --> 00:22:17,062
Supporting both of you.

382
00:22:17,063 --> 00:22:17,767
I’ll keep following your work.

383
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,600
Ploy.

384
00:22:49,733 --> 00:22:50,533
Hm?

385
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:54,404
This is the script for Shining Love
(Prakai Rak Song Jai).

386
00:22:54,404 --> 00:22:54,933
Hm?

387
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,400
But it’s not completely finished yet.

388
00:22:59,266 --> 00:23:02,924
Now that we’re performing a story from our real lives,

389
00:23:03,791 --> 00:23:05,391
I’m even more excited.

390
00:23:05,646 --> 00:23:07,686
More excited than any story
we’ve ever performed before.

391
00:23:08,866 --> 00:23:10,666
But you have to promise me first.

392
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:13,100
If you’re going to perform this story,

393
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,363
you must not look at the heroine’s face

394
00:23:16,771 --> 00:23:18,204
for more than ten seconds.

395
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,400
Huh?

396
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:20,800
Why?

397
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,591
Because the audience will know

398
00:23:24,050 --> 00:23:27,859
that the hero is really shy, not acting.

399
00:23:30,066 --> 00:23:31,963
Then who told the heroine

400
00:23:32,983 --> 00:23:34,519
to get more into it than the script?

401
00:23:37,357 --> 00:23:38,643
I don’t know.

402
00:23:39,066 --> 00:23:40,000
Crazy.

403
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:48,700
Oh.

404
00:23:49,312 --> 00:23:50,383
Speaking of work,

405
00:23:50,893 --> 00:23:53,379
today Khun Plub is coming with Lynchee.

406
00:23:53,685 --> 00:23:57,682
He said he wants to film
behind-the-scenes footage for research.

407
00:23:57,682 --> 00:24:00,481
And I’ll show him all the things

408
00:24:00,481 --> 00:24:02,536
we use for Likay. Is that okay?

409
00:24:03,829 --> 00:24:05,292
Mm.

410
00:24:06,066 --> 00:24:08,821
That’s fine, but don’t walk around
for too long.

411
00:24:08,821 --> 00:24:10,271
The sun is strong.

412
00:24:10,271 --> 00:24:12,755
And if there’s anything heavy to lift,

413
00:24:13,418 --> 00:24:14,792
call me.

414
00:24:15,866 --> 00:24:18,059
Oh, you…

415
00:24:18,926 --> 00:24:20,908
You’re always worried about me.

416
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,133
Of course I’m worried.

417
00:24:24,766 --> 00:24:25,866
This is only when…

418
00:24:30,133 --> 00:24:30,933
It’s okay.

419
00:24:33,766 --> 00:24:34,502
Everyone.

420
00:24:36,134 --> 00:24:37,788
Nine and Guy are back.

421
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:38,700
Hey.

422
00:25:09,333 --> 00:25:11,166
I thought you wouldn’t come back.

423
00:25:11,866 --> 00:25:13,266
Welcome home.

424
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:16,689
Welcome

425
00:25:16,689 --> 00:25:19,166
fully into
the Petchprakai family.

426
00:25:20,047 --> 00:25:20,925
Yes.

427
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,900
Once you enter this house, no backing out.

428
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:29,466
Of course we can’t back out. Only forward.

429
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:33,260
Oh, P’Nine.

430
00:25:33,821 --> 00:25:35,651
I’ll give you a tour of the troupe.

431
00:25:35,906 --> 00:25:37,974
This right here is our rehearsal hall.

432
00:25:37,974 --> 00:25:38,758
And over there is—

433
00:25:38,758 --> 00:25:39,993
No, no, no.

434
00:25:39,993 --> 00:25:41,105
I’ll do it.

435
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:43,590
Women always know every detail,
every corner first.

436
00:25:43,590 --> 00:25:44,868
I’ll give the tour.

437
00:25:44,868 --> 00:25:47,994
No, but you don’t know about
the sound and lighting systems.

438
00:25:47,994 --> 00:25:49,447
I’ll explain those too.

439
00:25:49,447 --> 00:25:51,700
They’re considered the troupe’s
classic systems, right?

440
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,775
Classic?

441
00:25:52,775 --> 00:25:55,124
What classic? Yesterday it was still flickering when we turned it on.

442
00:25:55,266 --> 00:25:58,800
No, it wasn’t my fault.
Someone walked past and it suddenly turned on.

443
00:25:59,133 --> 00:25:59,933
This is it.

444
00:26:00,466 --> 00:26:02,134
This kind of atmosphere

445
00:26:02,134 --> 00:26:03,366
is what truly feels like home.

446
00:26:05,166 --> 00:26:07,500
Yes, this is what I missed.

447
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,666
P’Plub.

448
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:17,700
Why are there so many people today?

449
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,600
I thought it was just a normal troupe rehearsal.

450
00:26:21,100 --> 00:26:22,943
P’Plub, you came on the perfect day.

451
00:26:22,943 --> 00:26:24,596
Today could be called

452
00:26:24,596 --> 00:26:27,200
the full-team Petchprakai Troupe.

453
00:26:28,666 --> 00:26:30,613
Guy and P’Nine

454
00:26:30,613 --> 00:26:33,600
gave Mother a huge surprise.

455
00:26:34,566 --> 00:26:35,933
Hello, Khun Lookplub.

456
00:26:36,466 --> 00:26:37,200
Hello.

457
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,706
My name is Tor Prakai.

458
00:26:38,706 --> 00:26:40,900
I’m one of the troupe’s first-generation members.

459
00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:42,918
And this is Khun Nine.

460
00:26:42,918 --> 00:26:44,700
He’s the newest member.

461
00:26:46,066 --> 00:26:46,964
Hello, everyone.

462
00:26:46,964 --> 00:26:49,622
I’m Lookplub. I just came back from Bangkok.

463
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,468
So I stopped by here right after.

464
00:26:51,468 --> 00:26:53,173
This morning, I interviewed a professor

465
00:26:53,173 --> 00:26:54,489
in contemporary culture.

466
00:26:54,693 --> 00:26:56,007
I got tons of information.

467
00:26:56,364 --> 00:26:58,811
So I’m fired up to collect information about the troupe

468
00:26:58,811 --> 00:27:00,070
for my thesis.

469
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:02,853
And I’d like to film some short clips
for your channel too.

470
00:27:03,210 --> 00:27:05,714
That’s great. You came at the perfect time.

471
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:08,789
Our house is about to
begin a new season.

472
00:27:08,789 --> 00:27:10,882
Just like Lynchee said.

473
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:13,800
P’Plub.

474
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:14,266
Yes?

475
00:27:14,266 --> 00:27:16,500
Could you please film a lot of me?

476
00:27:16,700 --> 00:27:18,100
People might misunderstand

477
00:27:18,266 --> 00:27:20,566
that this troupe’s second lead is
an NPC with no dialogue.

478
00:27:20,700 --> 00:27:21,566
That can’t happen.

479
00:27:21,666 --> 00:27:22,966
I need lots of scenes.

480
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:24,500
Hurry up.

481
00:27:24,733 --> 00:27:26,009
You want to be a star that badly?

482
00:27:26,009 --> 00:27:26,509
Yeah.

483
00:27:26,933 --> 00:27:28,000
Calm down first.

484
00:27:28,466 --> 00:27:30,533
You still have several levels to clear.

485
00:27:33,666 --> 00:27:35,166
Please take care of me.

486
00:27:35,533 --> 00:27:37,700
I’m interested in filming clips and vlogs too.

487
00:27:38,766 --> 00:27:39,366
Really?

488
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:41,278
Before this, Guy and I talked about

489
00:27:41,278 --> 00:27:43,943
wanting to do it,
but we never had the chance.

490
00:27:43,943 --> 00:27:47,300
So please let us be
in Khun Plub’s clip first.

491
00:27:47,866 --> 00:27:49,133
Of course. I’d be happy to.

492
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:51,284
Ploy will take

493
00:27:51,284 --> 00:27:53,591
Khun Plub,
backstage later.

494
00:27:53,591 --> 00:27:55,339
We just finished arranging everything.

495
00:27:55,339 --> 00:27:57,225
I think it should look beautiful on camera.

496
00:27:57,266 --> 00:27:58,119
I’d be glad to.

497
00:27:58,119 --> 00:28:00,966
Since I’m here, I’d like to gather
plenty of material.

498
00:28:02,300 --> 00:28:04,733
Then let me take one more
shot of everyone.

499
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:06,400
Sure.

500
00:28:06,766 --> 00:28:07,834
First of all,

501
00:28:07,834 --> 00:28:09,099
welcome

502
00:28:09,099 --> 00:28:11,064
the new members of our troupe

503
00:28:11,064 --> 00:28:12,166
officially.

504
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:13,991
Welcome.

505
00:28:13,991 --> 00:28:14,866
Yay!

506
00:28:15,333 --> 00:28:16,366
New members!

507
00:28:16,866 --> 00:28:18,100
Let’s take photos.

508
00:28:18,166 --> 00:28:19,133
Come on, let’s take photos.

509
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:22,220
(Lookplub) Smile, please.
(Lynchee) Over here, please.

510
00:28:23,933 --> 00:28:24,503
One.

511
00:28:24,503 --> 00:28:25,075
Two.

512
00:28:25,075 --> 00:28:25,575
Three.

513
00:28:39,366 --> 00:28:40,166
One more photo.

514
00:28:40,745 --> 00:28:41,245
One.

515
00:28:41,245 --> 00:28:41,817
Two.

516
00:28:41,818 --> 00:28:42,543
Three.

517
00:28:52,133 --> 00:28:53,733
This is the rehearsal hall.

518
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:56,533
It’s been the same hall since I was a kid.

519
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,300
Even the pillars are the same. Look.

520
00:28:59,733 --> 00:29:00,392
How is it?

521
00:29:00,392 --> 00:29:01,133
Wow.

522
00:29:01,733 --> 00:29:03,066
It feels so sacred.

523
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:08,883
Oh, hello.

524
00:29:08,884 --> 00:29:10,000
Hello.

525
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:10,906
And this person

526
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:13,918
is P’Samran, who handles the sound.

527
00:29:14,377 --> 00:29:15,889
If you ever hear the music going off-key,

528
00:29:16,450 --> 00:29:17,480
he’s the one

529
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:18,535
who fixes it.

530
00:29:19,759 --> 00:29:20,415
Hello.

531
00:29:21,537 --> 00:29:22,765
City actor.

532
00:29:23,581 --> 00:29:26,273
When you’re here, drink herbal water.
You’ll sing all night.

533
00:29:27,803 --> 00:29:30,294
Yes, sir. I promise.

534
00:29:33,533 --> 00:29:35,866
I’ll practice singing until I’m as good as you.

535
00:29:37,088 --> 00:29:38,439
Whoa.

536
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:41,471
I’m embarrassed. What are you saying?

537
00:29:50,300 --> 00:29:51,889
This place

538
00:29:53,113 --> 00:29:54,806
is where I began.

539
00:30:00,466 --> 00:30:03,533
And this is the script for Shining Love
(Prakai Rak Song Jai).

540
00:30:06,466 --> 00:30:08,366
This time, we have to make it a huge hit.

541
00:30:08,900 --> 00:30:10,483
Because this year’s troupe anniversary

542
00:30:10,483 --> 00:30:11,900
won’t be like any other time.

543
00:30:12,333 --> 00:30:13,133
Alright.

544
00:30:14,133 --> 00:30:16,366
First pair, start with Guy and Nine.

545
00:30:16,903 --> 00:30:17,988
Already?

546
00:30:17,988 --> 00:30:19,161
♪ And ask ♪

547
00:30:19,161 --> 00:30:21,166
♪ with deep ♪

548
00:30:21,167 --> 00:30:23,167
♪ concern ♪

549
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,596
But show me the eyes.

550
00:30:25,596 --> 00:30:27,166
What does concern look like?

551
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:35,466
Enough, enough.

552
00:30:35,733 --> 00:30:36,398
Ow.

553
00:30:36,398 --> 00:30:37,566
I only asked you to demonstrate.

554
00:30:38,133 --> 00:30:39,166
Ready, Lynchee?

555
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,400
Me first?

556
00:30:41,066 --> 00:30:44,416
♪ Never apart ♪

557
00:30:46,700 --> 00:30:47,848
Can I have one phrase?

558
00:30:47,848 --> 00:30:50,855
♪ Never apart ♪

559
00:30:50,856 --> 00:30:52,091
♪ far away ♪

560
00:30:52,092 --> 00:30:53,123
Oh.

561
00:30:53,481 --> 00:30:54,308
How is it?

562
00:30:54,527 --> 00:30:57,292
♪ Care for the royal son ♪

563
00:30:59,653 --> 00:31:01,041
How is it?

564
00:31:01,331 --> 00:31:01,831
How was it?

565
00:31:03,966 --> 00:31:05,262
I can’t believe it.

566
00:31:05,772 --> 00:31:06,879
You really did it.

567
00:31:06,879 --> 00:31:08,502
I thought you only came to be funny.

568
00:31:11,496 --> 00:31:12,147
Before,

569
00:31:12,912 --> 00:31:13,858
I used to do it.

570
00:31:15,898 --> 00:31:18,391
But after my parents passed away, I stopped.

571
00:31:19,156 --> 00:31:19,987
So I thought

572
00:31:20,752 --> 00:31:22,113
this time, I’d come back seriously again.

573
00:31:23,439 --> 00:31:27,293
For my parents and for this troupe too.

574
00:31:29,388 --> 00:31:30,775
Mm.

575
00:31:31,438 --> 00:31:31,957
Okay.

576
00:31:32,824 --> 00:31:34,171
Today, I give you full marks.

577
00:31:35,125 --> 00:31:36,659
Then that means

578
00:31:37,220 --> 00:31:38,806
we’re officially boyfriend and girlfriend now,
right?

579
00:31:40,502 --> 00:31:41,410
Huh?

580
00:31:43,333 --> 00:31:44,745
Are we…

581
00:31:44,745 --> 00:31:45,687
Are we boyfriend and girlfriend now?

582
00:31:46,066 --> 00:31:46,866
So delayed.

583
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,966
If this were a game, I’d think you lagged out.

584
00:31:49,133 --> 00:31:49,666
Hey.

585
00:31:49,666 --> 00:31:51,533
Wait, then I’ll switch servers.

586
00:31:51,566 --> 00:31:52,900
So we won’t lag anymore.

587
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,166
If the internet drops, my girlfriend might run away.

588
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:03,644
Okay, everyone did very well today.

589
00:32:04,154 --> 00:32:05,617
You can go take a break first.

590
00:32:05,923 --> 00:32:07,902
Then this afternoon,
we’ll continue reading the script.

591
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:13,218
Khun Plub, will you keep filming?

592
00:32:13,575 --> 00:32:15,657
Or save it to film another day?

593
00:32:15,966 --> 00:32:17,657
I think I’ll film a little more.

594
00:32:18,218 --> 00:32:19,810
I want to keep these moments.

595
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,162
It feels like there’s something in every day.

596
00:32:22,876 --> 00:32:24,823
When I see everyone together,

597
00:32:25,384 --> 00:32:28,145
it feels like the troupe has truly come alive.

598
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:32,464
At this time in the evening,

599
00:32:32,974 --> 00:32:34,561
the light is really beautiful, Khun Plub.

600
00:32:35,479 --> 00:32:38,431
Would you like to try filming from other angles?

601
00:32:39,235 --> 00:32:39,962
Yes.

602
00:32:40,523 --> 00:32:41,684
I want to film now.

603
00:32:41,888 --> 00:32:43,480
When everyone isn’t acting,

604
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:44,927
but still feels alive on stage.

605
00:32:44,927 --> 00:32:45,733
Okay.

606
00:32:46,100 --> 00:32:47,966
Then let’s rehearse a little more.

607
00:32:49,266 --> 00:32:51,766
Hey, didn’t you just say we could rest?

608
00:32:52,066 --> 00:32:53,333
Mm.

609
00:32:54,266 --> 00:32:55,100
I changed my mind.

610
00:32:55,101 --> 00:32:56,200
Huh?

611
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:58,166
I just want to try something new.

612
00:33:08,900 --> 00:33:09,991
With that look,

613
00:33:10,501 --> 00:33:12,151
P’Phet definitely has something on his mind.

614
00:33:14,466 --> 00:33:15,266
What?

615
00:33:27,866 --> 00:33:28,879
Hello, everyone.

616
00:33:29,338 --> 00:33:30,292
Welcome, everyone,

617
00:33:30,292 --> 00:33:33,121
to Likay Streamer Family.

618
00:33:33,121 --> 00:33:35,530
Today, I’m back again
with P’Pleng himself.

619
00:33:35,530 --> 00:33:37,643
Today, I’m here to announce that

620
00:33:37,643 --> 00:33:41,125
from today on, I’ll be a real
Likay streamer.

621
00:33:43,300 --> 00:33:44,491
And one more thing

622
00:33:44,491 --> 00:33:47,149
that’s very important and I’d like to, uh,

623
00:33:48,679 --> 00:33:52,030
announce to everyone.

624
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:56,400
It’s a major patch update

625
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,870
in my life, you could say.

626
00:33:58,870 --> 00:34:00,588
And that is…

627
00:34:00,588 --> 00:34:02,014
Uh…

628
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:05,141
I have a girlfriend, everyone.

629
00:34:08,333 --> 00:34:09,133
How is it?

630
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:12,333
Keep the comments coming.

631
00:34:13,066 --> 00:34:13,866
Hello.

632
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:16,600
I’m Lynchee, Pleng Chai’s girlfriend.

633
00:34:18,666 --> 00:34:21,400
Today, may I join everyone
for duo ranked.

634
00:34:22,333 --> 00:34:25,230
I don’t have much to say except

635
00:34:25,230 --> 00:34:27,733
everyone, prepare to lose to Lynchee today.

636
00:34:29,066 --> 00:34:29,900
Be careful.

637
00:34:30,466 --> 00:34:31,866
And let me introduce her again.

638
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:34,600
This is Miss Lynchee
from the Petchprakai Troupe.

639
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:35,600
Whoa.

640
00:34:37,266 --> 00:34:38,466
Uh, everyone.

641
00:34:38,866 --> 00:34:40,512
Please don’t misunderstand me.

642
00:34:40,512 --> 00:34:41,012
I mean,

643
00:34:42,066 --> 00:34:43,600
I didn’t force her to go live.

644
00:34:43,900 --> 00:34:45,262
She came in herself. I knew nothing.

645
00:34:45,262 --> 00:34:46,700
Hey, what do you mean saying that?

646
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:48,300
You don’t want to go live together?

647
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,300
No, not like that.

648
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:53,666
Start the game already.

649
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,200
Yes.

650
00:34:55,666 --> 00:34:57,333
If anyone gets matched with us,

651
00:34:58,313 --> 00:35:00,313
be careful.

652
00:35:02,133 --> 00:35:03,600
Go.

653
00:35:04,366 --> 00:35:07,066
Go, go left.

654
00:35:09,566 --> 00:35:11,733
Die, die, die. Die.

655
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Done.

656
00:35:13,166 --> 00:35:13,966
Great.

657
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,100
How was that?

658
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:16,566
Is anyone here?

659
00:35:16,666 --> 00:35:18,100
Did I kill anyone here?

660
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:24,949
Hello, everyone. Today,
we’re at the Petchprakai Likay Troupe.

661
00:35:24,949 --> 00:35:26,214
Today is rehearsal day

662
00:35:26,214 --> 00:35:28,300
number two.
Let’s follow along, everyone.

663
00:35:40,966 --> 00:35:41,733
Go in.

664
00:35:41,733 --> 00:35:42,566
Be more persistent.

665
00:35:43,333 --> 00:35:44,443
I’ll brush him off a bit.

666
00:35:44,443 --> 00:35:45,791
No, don’t touch my chin.

667
00:35:45,791 --> 00:35:46,700
Something like that. Go away.

668
00:35:46,966 --> 00:35:47,593
Don’t.

669
00:35:47,593 --> 00:35:48,200
Just brush the hand away.

670
00:35:48,700 --> 00:35:49,500
Brush the hand.

671
00:35:50,455 --> 00:35:51,333
One more time.

672
00:35:51,334 --> 00:35:52,008
Calm down.

673
00:35:53,975 --> 00:35:55,006
Oh.

674
00:35:55,007 --> 00:35:56,344
You’re trying to court him, right?

675
00:35:56,617 --> 00:35:57,366
Can I?

676
00:35:57,366 --> 00:35:58,166
Yes.

677
00:35:58,167 --> 00:35:59,453
(Phet Thae) Cute.
(Ploy Ying) Great chemistry.

678
00:36:03,733 --> 00:36:06,689
Okay, then I’ll let you take a break first.

679
00:36:06,689 --> 00:36:09,014
Go drink some water and rest.

680
00:36:09,779 --> 00:36:10,770
Then we’ll come back and rehearse again.

681
00:36:10,770 --> 00:36:11,581
Okay.

682
00:36:11,583 --> 00:36:12,500
Pleng.

683
00:36:12,500 --> 00:36:13,900
Lynchee too, go rest.

684
00:36:14,766 --> 00:36:15,966
(Pleng Chai) Eat snacks.
(Phet Thae) Don’t forget to practice singing.

685
00:36:16,266 --> 00:36:17,200
Hey, come on. Let’s go.

686
00:36:17,366 --> 00:36:18,700
Hey, come on. Let’s go eat snacks.

687
00:36:19,533 --> 00:36:21,500
How was it? Is everything okay?

688
00:36:22,900 --> 00:36:24,562
It looks like it should go well, Ploy.

689
00:36:25,225 --> 00:36:26,500
Everyone seems very determined.

690
00:36:26,733 --> 00:36:27,400
Mm.

691
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:28,777
It’s like I said.

692
00:36:29,185 --> 00:36:31,045
I’ll make Shining Love (Prakai Rak Song Jai)

693
00:36:31,264 --> 00:36:34,094
shine as brightly as possible.

694
00:36:35,471 --> 00:36:36,717
So more people can see it.

695
00:36:38,043 --> 00:36:38,543
That’s good.

696
00:36:43,466 --> 00:36:44,201
P’Phet.

697
00:36:45,986 --> 00:36:47,586
Everything that happened

698
00:36:48,810 --> 00:36:51,726
may seem like bad luck,

699
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:54,042
but when I think about it,

700
00:36:54,399 --> 00:36:56,419
maybe it could be good luck too.

701
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:02,030
Good luck that we’re still together, right?

702
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,000
Yes.

703
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:06,766
If that hadn’t happened,

704
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:09,733
we probably wouldn’t have
gathered together like this.

705
00:37:10,700 --> 00:37:11,566
We wouldn’t be here.

706
00:37:12,933 --> 00:37:14,300
We wouldn’t be starting over together.

707
00:37:18,966 --> 00:37:21,000
Was being with Petchprakai really that terrible?

708
00:37:22,266 --> 00:37:23,500
Even after I gave you everything?

709
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:24,766
I taught you to sing. I taught you to dance.

710
00:37:24,900 --> 00:37:25,508
I did everything

711
00:37:25,508 --> 00:37:26,766
so you could become a good Likay hero.

712
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:27,900
But I didn’t want to be one.

713
00:37:31,133 --> 00:37:32,200
I miss home so much.

714
00:37:33,766 --> 00:37:35,166
I know I have to keep fighting.

715
00:37:36,933 --> 00:37:38,966
I want to go back with pride.

716
00:37:40,533 --> 00:37:41,333
Guy.

717
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:44,133
Guy, when I looked at your face today,

718
00:37:45,933 --> 00:37:48,300
I’d never seen you
this happy before.

719
00:37:56,533 --> 00:37:57,143
I’m

720
00:37:58,418 --> 00:37:59,952
about to invite the two of you

721
00:38:00,819 --> 00:38:02,921
to perform in Shining Love (Prakai Rak Song Jai)
with us.

722
00:38:04,196 --> 00:38:05,568
Then announce it.

723
00:38:07,100 --> 00:38:08,700
We definitely won’t disappear.

724
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:16,933
What Ploy said is true.

725
00:38:18,566 --> 00:38:20,559
Sometimes bad things

726
00:38:21,222 --> 00:38:22,756
are just a test.

727
00:38:23,011 --> 00:38:24,097
They make us realize

728
00:38:25,474 --> 00:38:29,198
whether we still want to move forward.

729
00:38:31,442 --> 00:38:33,138
And we chose to stay here

730
00:38:34,413 --> 00:38:37,521
and keep walking forward together.

731
00:38:38,543 --> 00:38:39,268
Right?

732
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:44,054
But if you want to keep walking,

733
00:38:45,227 --> 00:38:46,446
don’t forget to practice

734
00:38:46,446 --> 00:38:47,899
your own lines too.

735
00:38:47,899 --> 00:38:49,645
Deputy Leader.

736
00:38:49,645 --> 00:38:50,760
Yes, Leader.

737
00:38:51,866 --> 00:38:53,400
Nice save.

738
00:38:53,766 --> 00:38:54,600
Not seeing it means…?

739
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:56,103
It means…

740
00:38:56,103 --> 00:38:57,933
it exists. I’ve been practicing at home.

741
00:38:58,800 --> 00:38:59,370
Are you sure?

742
00:38:59,370 --> 00:38:59,966
Of course.

743
00:39:00,300 --> 00:39:01,266
Then sing it for me.

744
00:39:08,166 --> 00:39:08,666
Here.

745
00:39:08,972 --> 00:39:11,977
These are sweets for Khun Lynchee.

746
00:39:11,977 --> 00:39:13,606
Please accept them.

747
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,800
Thank you, Khun Pleng Chai.

748
00:39:16,700 --> 00:39:17,933
Oh, so many.

749
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,266
Lady by the canal,

750
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,666
your fair face glows beneath the sun.

751
00:39:31,100 --> 00:39:31,966
These sweets

752
00:39:32,733 --> 00:39:34,466
could never rival the sweetness of your heart.

753
00:39:35,966 --> 00:39:37,600
Should your temper flare once more,

754
00:39:38,666 --> 00:39:41,166
I shall peel coconuts for you every day.

755
00:39:42,900 --> 00:39:44,600
Oh, my Likay hero.

756
00:39:45,333 --> 00:39:47,374
Of course, a Likay hero.

757
00:39:47,374 --> 00:39:50,066
And here is my Likay heroine.

758
00:39:52,333 --> 00:39:53,133
You know,

759
00:39:53,700 --> 00:39:55,000
even though we’re already dating,

760
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:56,397
I still want to

761
00:39:56,907 --> 00:39:58,910
court you every single day.

762
00:39:59,733 --> 00:40:00,479
So sweet.

763
00:40:01,244 --> 00:40:02,374
I can’t even argue.

764
00:40:02,374 --> 00:40:03,166
Then don’t argue.

765
00:40:03,933 --> 00:40:05,000
Just smile.

766
00:40:11,133 --> 00:40:11,831
You know,

767
00:40:13,922 --> 00:40:16,016
I’m really happy.

768
00:40:16,934 --> 00:40:21,975
Just being together, enjoying the view,

769
00:40:22,689 --> 00:40:23,802
and eating sweets together,

770
00:40:24,516 --> 00:40:26,055
I think this alone is already wonderful.

771
00:40:27,598 --> 00:40:28,782
Me too.

772
00:40:30,666 --> 00:40:31,600
But you know what?

773
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,733
We can’t keep
getting fat together.

774
00:40:36,500 --> 00:40:37,933
Don’t joke with the truth.

775
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:39,733
Soon our Likay costumes won’t fit.

776
00:40:39,866 --> 00:40:41,066
After this one, then we diet.

777
00:40:41,266 --> 00:40:42,600
Okay, agreed.

778
00:40:45,366 --> 00:40:46,393
Do you feel like

779
00:40:46,801 --> 00:40:49,733
P’Lookplub has been acting strange lately?

780
00:40:53,066 --> 00:40:53,866
Strange how?

781
00:40:54,800 --> 00:41:00,500
I don’t know. Whenever P’Plub is with P’Ploy,

782
00:41:00,933 --> 00:41:02,784
he smiles a lot.

783
00:41:03,549 --> 00:41:06,239
He smiles, looks away, then smiles again.

784
00:41:06,966 --> 00:41:08,800
And whenever P’Phet comes in,

785
00:41:09,733 --> 00:41:10,837
I feel like P’Phet gets

786
00:41:11,551 --> 00:41:16,444
all still, like he’s swallowing

787
00:41:16,903 --> 00:41:18,155
something.

788
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:21,954
Swallowing what? Rice?

789
00:41:22,668 --> 00:41:26,204
Or swallowing jealousy?

790
00:41:27,615 --> 00:41:28,865
What are you saying?

791
00:41:29,375 --> 00:41:31,459
This will become news like
when P’Ploy went to the hospital.

792
00:41:34,643 --> 00:41:35,930
People will misunderstand.

793
00:41:35,930 --> 00:41:36,758
I was just teasing.

794
00:41:36,758 --> 00:41:37,891
No, no, no.

795
00:41:37,892 --> 00:41:38,974
Okay, okay.

796
00:41:39,778 --> 00:41:41,472
Keep talking nonsense and you’ll get it.

797
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:12,800
Are you tired?

798
00:42:13,766 --> 00:42:15,166
You rehearsed hard today.

799
00:42:16,966 --> 00:42:17,766
I’m tired.

800
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:20,100
But I’m fine.

801
00:42:20,966 --> 00:42:23,100
Just having you beside me like this

802
00:42:23,366 --> 00:42:24,166
makes me okay.

803
00:42:25,466 --> 00:42:26,366
You’re saying that again.

804
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:28,866
You’ll make me blush.

805
00:42:31,066 --> 00:42:32,066
So what if you blush?

806
00:42:32,533 --> 00:42:33,766
I’m telling the truth.

807
00:42:46,666 --> 00:42:47,466
Hey.

808
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:51,100
We’ve been through
so much together.

809
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:56,679
At first,

810
00:42:57,393 --> 00:42:59,077
I thought I wouldn’t be able to stay.

811
00:43:00,709 --> 00:43:03,220
But now I understand

812
00:43:04,550 --> 00:43:06,163
why I could.

813
00:43:08,866 --> 00:43:09,366
Why?

814
00:43:12,466 --> 00:43:14,200
Because I had you beside me.

815
00:43:22,366 --> 00:43:23,206
Thank you

816
00:43:24,073 --> 00:43:25,560
for still holding my hand.

817
00:43:27,039 --> 00:43:28,537
And I believe

818
00:43:29,404 --> 00:43:31,602
that as long as we keep holding hands like this,

819
00:43:33,642 --> 00:43:35,204
no matter how many times we have to start over,

820
00:43:35,765 --> 00:43:37,653
there’s nothing to fear.

821
00:43:42,266 --> 00:43:43,533
I’m not afraid anymore either.

822
00:44:45,866 --> 00:44:47,666
You secretly added more sugar again, didn’t you?

823
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:49,000
P’Phet.

824
00:44:49,100 --> 00:44:50,200
I could smell the sweetness.

825
00:44:50,900 --> 00:44:52,366
When did you come in?

826
00:44:54,600 --> 00:44:56,208
I just wanted to know

827
00:44:56,514 --> 00:44:59,906
what Ploy made for me today.

828
00:45:01,166 --> 00:45:03,100
I almost spilled everything.

829
00:45:03,700 --> 00:45:04,966
You have to finish all of this.

830
00:45:07,966 --> 00:45:08,873
You…

831
00:45:09,638 --> 00:45:11,419
always come in to tease me.

832
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:14,966
Because when Ploy gets startled,

833
00:45:16,166 --> 00:45:16,966
you’re cute.

834
00:45:20,333 --> 00:45:21,133
Crazy.

835
00:45:21,733 --> 00:45:22,700
Go away.

836
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,866
I’ll end up pounding everything wrong.

837
00:45:27,733 --> 00:45:29,400
What you’re pounding now, is it right?

838
00:45:30,745 --> 00:45:31,600
Yes.

839
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:34,333
Then let me stay close
enough to smell the sweetness.

840
00:45:35,533 --> 00:45:36,333
Can I?

841
00:45:36,533 --> 00:45:37,366
Fine.

842
00:45:46,866 --> 00:45:49,100
Khun Plub sent another clip for us to watch.

843
00:45:51,733 --> 00:45:52,533
What clip?

844
00:45:53,500 --> 00:45:54,933
A behind-the-scenes clip of the troupe.

845
00:45:55,500 --> 00:45:57,916
He said if we watch it and think it’s okay,

846
00:45:57,916 --> 00:45:59,400
he’ll edit it into the first clip.

847
00:46:01,766 --> 00:46:05,013
Mm, it’s a behind-the-scenes clip of the troupe.

848
00:46:05,013 --> 00:46:06,123
Have you watched it yet?

849
00:46:07,092 --> 00:46:10,969
If you approve it,
he’ll post it tonight.

850
00:46:16,766 --> 00:46:17,733
I’ll watch it.

851
00:46:20,333 --> 00:46:21,766
His skills are good, though.

852
00:46:22,100 --> 00:46:23,533
He’s really good at capturing footage.

853
00:46:25,333 --> 00:46:27,566
True. He’s very diligent.

854
00:46:28,166 --> 00:46:29,666
And his shots are beautiful too.

855
00:46:30,866 --> 00:46:33,400
Tomorrow he’ll come film more.

856
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:35,327
Oh, he told me

857
00:46:35,327 --> 00:46:37,133
he wants to interview you too.

858
00:46:42,166 --> 00:46:43,766
It’s so cute. Looks good, see?

859
00:47:01,133 --> 00:47:03,361
Today, we’ll rehearse Shining Love
(Prakai Rak Song Jai)

860
00:47:04,330 --> 00:47:05,357
seriously.

861
00:47:07,800 --> 00:47:08,600
Pleng.

862
00:47:09,300 --> 00:47:09,800
Yes?

863
00:47:09,800 --> 00:47:11,519
Pleng is the first person who has to rehearse.

864
00:47:11,519 --> 00:47:12,400
Get up.

865
00:47:26,100 --> 00:47:27,400
Pleng, go review over there first.

866
00:47:27,700 --> 00:47:28,900
Go practice by yourself over there.

867
00:47:30,133 --> 00:47:31,066
It’s okay.

868
00:47:31,466 --> 00:47:33,300
Nine, come dance for me.

869
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:39,807
Guy,

870
00:47:40,317 --> 00:47:42,507
go help check Nine’s dance.

871
00:47:42,507 --> 00:47:46,110
I think the legs
aren’t quite coordinated.

872
00:47:46,492 --> 00:47:48,980
Let Guy help you. Go over there.

873
00:47:49,617 --> 00:47:53,606
♪ With graceful artistry ♪

874
00:47:55,228 --> 00:47:57,228
You have to listen to the rhythm too. Again.

875
00:47:59,233 --> 00:48:01,233
Ow.

876
00:48:01,978 --> 00:48:03,315
I can’t take it anymore today.

877
00:48:05,333 --> 00:48:06,566
I can’t either.

878
00:48:08,302 --> 00:48:09,282
Are you okay?

879
00:48:10,001 --> 00:48:12,001
Ow.

880
00:48:16,086 --> 00:48:19,157
It’s so hard.

881
00:48:20,166 --> 00:48:22,241
It’s just “graceful artistry.”

882
00:48:25,892 --> 00:48:26,872
Hey.

883
00:48:31,466 --> 00:48:32,333
Ping Pong Chae.

884
00:48:48,333 --> 00:48:49,900
If you have something to say, say it.

885
00:48:50,900 --> 00:48:52,933
We’re sorry.

886
00:48:55,566 --> 00:48:56,718
I’m sorry.

887
00:48:57,126 --> 00:48:58,759
Back then, we were addicted to online gambling,

888
00:48:59,116 --> 00:49:00,391
so we abandoned our troupe.

889
00:49:00,748 --> 00:49:02,455
It was our fault.

890
00:49:59,166 --> 00:50:01,133
How did we even get to this point?

891
00:50:03,900 --> 00:50:04,855
At least

892
00:50:06,079 --> 00:50:07,955
we have a place to sleep.

893
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:32,800
You can sell anything,

894
00:50:34,466 --> 00:50:36,100
but not this.

895
00:50:39,900 --> 00:50:40,700
Put it away.

896
00:51:01,466 --> 00:51:04,366
Work hard, so you can stay here
long-term.

897
00:51:05,466 --> 00:51:06,782
Yes, we

898
00:51:06,782 --> 00:51:08,266
will work hard from now on.

899
00:51:08,733 --> 00:51:09,533
Very good.

900
00:51:13,533 --> 00:51:14,344
It’s clean now.

901
00:51:14,821 --> 00:51:16,821
(Ping) Is it?
(Chae) Scrub properly. Hurry.

902
00:51:28,166 --> 00:51:29,733
What should we do next?

903
00:51:35,066 --> 00:51:35,670
Should we

904
00:51:36,486 --> 00:51:37,647
go back?

905
00:51:39,075 --> 00:51:40,574
Back to everyone.

906
00:51:46,700 --> 00:51:47,666
It’s time

907
00:51:49,500 --> 00:51:51,466
we return something important.

908
00:52:06,592 --> 00:52:07,776
It’s okay.

909
00:52:08,964 --> 00:52:09,740
Come on.

910
00:52:17,366 --> 00:52:19,200
Do you think saying just that will make it over?

911
00:52:21,566 --> 00:52:23,500
If you still don’t stop stealing money,

912
00:52:24,133 --> 00:52:25,800
still don’t stop online gambling,

913
00:52:27,166 --> 00:52:29,133
I’ll send all of you to the police.

914
00:52:34,700 --> 00:52:35,966
Calm down, P’Phet.

915
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:43,333
Give them one more chance.

916
00:52:45,566 --> 00:52:47,466
If someone has to take responsibility for what went missing,

917
00:52:48,766 --> 00:52:50,200
I’ll take responsibility myself.

918
00:53:07,733 --> 00:53:08,900
If anything happens, tell me.

919
00:53:12,533 --> 00:53:13,766
I’m always ready to help.

920
00:53:24,900 --> 00:53:25,766
Thank you.

921
00:53:26,266 --> 00:53:27,466
I’m sorry.

922
00:53:39,766 --> 00:53:41,200
Online gambling must end.

923
00:53:42,166 --> 00:53:43,166
A burden on the land.

924
00:53:51,333 --> 00:53:53,606
Good. Since everyone’s here,

925
00:53:53,606 --> 00:53:54,578
let’s eat.

926
00:53:54,578 --> 00:53:55,573
Come on, let’s eat.

927
00:53:55,573 --> 00:53:58,882
Stop crying and go eat.
Let’s eat dinner.

928
00:53:58,882 --> 00:54:00,043
Go. Go eat.

929
00:54:00,043 --> 00:54:00,646
Come on.

930
00:54:00,646 --> 00:54:01,401
Hello, Auntie Headman.

931
00:54:01,401 --> 00:54:03,333
(Ploy Ying) Hello.
(Phet Thae) Hello.

932
00:54:12,403 --> 00:54:13,077
Ping.

933
00:54:14,043 --> 00:54:14,733
Get a plate for…

934
00:54:14,733 --> 00:54:15,533
Stop crying.

935
00:54:15,534 --> 00:54:16,259
For Auntie.

936
00:54:19,366 --> 00:54:21,100
Who cooked today?

937
00:54:22,558 --> 00:54:23,844
Who else?

938
00:54:24,153 --> 00:54:26,153
Taste it and you’ll know.

939
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:28,800
Hello.

940
00:55:30,366 --> 00:55:32,333
Don’t you recognize my voice, Phet Thae?

941
00:55:32,800 --> 00:55:34,166
It’s Boss Ah.

942
00:55:35,966 --> 00:55:36,766
Uh.

943
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:38,600
Boss.

944
00:55:41,166 --> 00:55:42,491
Our troupe

945
00:55:42,491 --> 00:55:44,829
has already paid back a lot in installments.

946
00:55:46,512 --> 00:55:48,710
But what you asked me to do,

947
00:55:49,271 --> 00:55:50,651
to transfer the final lump sum all at once,

948
00:55:50,651 --> 00:55:53,227
our troupe really doesn’t have it.

949
00:55:53,333 --> 00:55:55,058
But if we can keep paying in installments like before,

950
00:55:55,058 --> 00:55:56,718
we can definitely handle it.

951
00:55:57,432 --> 00:56:00,830
Even though our troupe is gaining attention
and getting work again,

952
00:56:00,830 --> 00:56:04,725
the expenses are
still heavy.

953
00:56:06,300 --> 00:56:07,100
Hmph.

954
00:56:07,366 --> 00:56:08,166
Installments?

955
00:56:08,533 --> 00:56:11,366
I’ve let you pay in installments
for long enough, haven’t I, young Phet?

956
00:56:13,100 --> 00:56:16,066
Or should I send someone
to visit your troupe house?

957
00:56:16,366 --> 00:56:17,800
Please don’t hurt anyone, Boss.

958
00:56:18,566 --> 00:56:19,733
I… I’m begging you.

959
00:56:20,733 --> 00:56:22,966
I’ll find a way
to pay you back for sure.

960
00:56:23,533 --> 00:56:24,966
I’ll hurry and find the money for you, Boss.

961
00:56:26,766 --> 00:56:28,510
I’m giving you until the end of this month.

962
00:56:29,275 --> 00:56:30,319
If there’s no money,

963
00:56:30,319 --> 00:56:33,965
we’ll see what else I can take instead.

964
00:56:57,866 --> 00:56:59,333
Two and a half million left.

965
00:56:59,900 --> 00:57:01,316
If I still don’t get the money,

966
00:57:02,438 --> 00:57:04,900
your troupe will be seized, Nephew Phet.

967
00:57:05,400 --> 00:57:06,366
Then let’s help each other.

968
00:57:06,666 --> 00:57:08,590
Let’s make Shining Love (Prakai Rak Song Jai)
the best it can be.

969
00:57:08,590 --> 00:57:11,466
Let it be the stage these siblings
are most proud of in their lives.

970
00:57:11,966 --> 00:57:14,246
The Petchprakai Troupe will never surrender again.

971
00:57:14,246 --> 00:57:16,400
We will keep standing on this stage.

972
00:57:18,100 --> 00:57:19,500
Marry me, Ploy.
